problems.description:
Predict the output — `finally` always runs, even after `return`:

```java
static String test() {
    try { return "try"; }
    finally { System.out.println("finally"); }
}
System.out.println(test());
```

**Output:**
finally
try

**Key insight:** `finally` executes before the return value is delivered. If `finally` has its own `return`, it overrides the `try` return.

