    }
}

problems.description:
Implement an **exception translation layer**: catch low-level `SQLException` and re-throw as domain-specific `DataAccessException` with a user-friendly message.

**Example:**
try { jdbcCall(); }
catch (SQLException e) {
    throw new DataAccessException("Failed to load user", e);
}

DataAccessException.getCause() => original SQLException
DataAccessException.getMessage() => "Failed to load user"

**Key insight:** Preserve the cause chain (`super(message, cause)`) — never swallow exceptions.

